Measure of Motion Severity (MMS) is the instantaneous value of the ratio of the total acceleration in the plane of the helideck divided by the component of the total acceleration normal to the helideck. Motion Severity Index is the maximum value of MMS measured during the previous 20 minutes, converted to the form of a dynamic helideck slope in degrees, and then multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest whole number.
